records.addlTxt:
Defendant Brandon Jay Escamilla in court with attorney Enku Edgar Lin.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered count dismissed and read-in for sentencing purposes.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions:  
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  Participate in cognitive therapy;
*  Perform 15 hours of community service;
*  Participate in parenting classes;
*  Maintain full time work/school;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

Court will allow probation to be terminated after 9 months if the defendant successfully completes all conditions of probation.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
